    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Snows of Yesteryear? Today They're in Machinery,'' by Peter Applebome (Our Towns, Dec. 6):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Snows of Yesteryear? Today They're in Machinery,'' by Peter Applebome (Our Towns, Dec. 6):</p>
        <p>Ski resort managers understand that global warming is responsible for the shorter, milder and unpredictable winters that are disastrous to snowfall, skiing and their profits.</p>
        <p>Their solution: Fire up the snowmakers that spew out tons of greenhouse gases every day, speeding up climate change and hastening the demise of their own industry.</p>
        <p>Surely economic self-interest, if not concern for a planetary future that Windham's manager acknowledges is ''terrifying,'' might lead them to rethink this suicidal business strategy.</p>
        <p>Jeanne Bergman  New York, Dec. 7, 2006</p>
      </block>
